claim.claim-text:
1. A method for carrying out combustion in a furnace having porous walls comprising: 
a) providing a combustion zone containing an atmosphere of furnace gases; 
b) injecting a low velocity oxidant stream through at least one oxidant injection side of the porous walls into the combustion zone; 
c) injecting a fuel stream through at least one fuel injection side directed toward the oxidant injection side in the combustion zone; and 
d) mixing the low velocity oxidant and fuel stream in said combustion zone to create a flame with reduced flame temperature.

8. A method for carrying out combustion in a furnace having porous walls comprising: 
a) providing a combustion zone containing an atmosphere of furnace gases; 
b) injecting a low velocity fuel stream through at least one fuel injection side of the porous walls into the combustion zone; 
c) injecting an oxidant stream through at least one oxidant injection side directed toward the fuel injection side in the combustion zone; and 
d) mixing the diluted fuel and oxidant mixtures to create a flame with reduced flame temperature.
